Court costs, fees, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
1) Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay DNA surcharge on each count;
2) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
3) No contact with the victims or their families, their place of residence, employment or school. No contact includes no third party contact;
4) Register and comply with the sex offender registry;
5) Obtain/comply with sex offender treatment; 
6) Participate in a cognitive therapy class at the institution; 
7) Participate in a psychological evaluation in order for the agent to determine treatment needs;
8) No access to internet during period of initial confinement. 
9) No use of social media accounts;
10) If defendant owns any electronic devices with internet capabilities, it is to be made available to agent for inspection upon demand;

Court will determine restitution at a future restitution hearing. 

